ers and great friends. My wife and I cried when we left.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;I still speak with fans on Instagram and I want to see Newcastle back at the top and to even win the Champions League - why not? I want to come back to see one game there - maybe when Thomas [his son] is playing there.&quot;"},{"pid":"3aec60d0dc0dadb7d3a9ee80faadc73cd557f378","tid":2013132,"uid":30182,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"51ca972f4c1859b8466935f05907cf77621a53c6","tid":2013132,"uid":210937,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-05-12T06:29:17.000Z","msg":"Laurent Robert on the Newcastle United takeover<br />\n<img src=\"https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/article18158005.ece/ALTERNATES/s510b/0_GettyImages-1006866.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chroniclelive.co.uk%2Fsport%2Ffootball%2Ffootball-news%2Farticle18158005.ece%2FALTERNATES%2Fs510b%2F0_GettyImages-1006866.jpg&h=5cfdd7b3&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\nSpeaking to Sky Sports, Laurent Robert said: &quot;I'm very happy about the takeover because I think Newcastle can go back to a very high level. I think the club is big enough for that.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;When I arrived at Newcastle, their position in the table was not very good.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Then in the first season we finished fourth, and the season after that we were third.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;We played in the Champions League and that's why you want to play football. I wanted to play in the competition every year when I was at Paris Saint-Germain.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Sir Bobby Robson was our manager and I played with great guys like Alan Shearer and Gary Speed. They were great players and great friends. My wife and I cried when we left.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;I still speak with fans on Instagram and I want to see Newcastle back at the top and to even win the Champions League - why not? I want to come back to see one game there - maybe when Thomas [his son] is playing 